Common.Strapline.Common.Text: F&B OPPORTUNITY - HEART OF CHATSWOOD COMMERCIAL CORE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located in the heart of Chatswood CBD just 10 kms from Sydney CBD, this property offers a solid retail investment in one of the strongest retail markets in Sydney. The property is fully leased to five (5) quality tenants including TAB Corp and the popular Cafe New York. This rare offering provides the opportunity to acquire a 100% freehold interest in one of the most prominent positions in the tightly held retail market of Chatswood.

Investment Highlights Include:

* Exceptional position in a prominent location
* Newly renovated and upgraded building
* Secure and sustainable income stream
* Excellent tenant profile
* Strategic retail investment

Location:
Chatswood is located approximately 10 kms from Sydney CBD across the Sydney harbour on the North Shore. Chatswood CBD is conveniently situated on the eastern side of Pacific Highway the major arterial road connecting Northern Sydney and the Central Coast of NSW to Sydney CBD

Position:
Prominently positioned on Chatswood Mall (Victoria Avenue) immediately adjoining the Chatswood Transport Interchange (CTI). The mall connects CTI to the shopping and entertainment precincts within the area the property receives exposure to more than 35,000 pedistrians a day. The property also has direct access into the CTI on Level 2, 430 Victoria Avenue

Property Description:
Recently rebuilt two (2) storey building at 426-428 Victoria Avenue comprises of two tenancies including a 10 year lease to Cafe New York. The adjoining 430 Victoria Avenue comprises a three (3) storey building at that includes three separate tenancies including a new 10 year lease to TAB corp as well as a Government tenant. At grade parking space/loading dock located at the rear through Post Lane.

Net Income:
$841,719 pa approximately

Site Area:
588 sqm approximately

Lettable Area:
1,346 sqm approximately

Gross Building Area:
1,584 sqm approximately

CBRE, under instructions from the Receivers & Managers, Peter Marsden and Richard Stone of RSM Australia Partners, are pleased to present Lot 6 & 8, 7 Help Street to market. The property is a large retail strata located in the highly popular suburb of Chatswood. Currently tenanted by the well-established Fook Yuen Seafood Restaurant, the yum cha venue is a prime offering to both investors and owner occupiers in a rapidly growing area.

Lot 6 & 8, 7 Help Street benefits from the following features:

- Tenanted by Fook Yuen Seafood Restaurant, a Cantonese yum cha venue with a long business history at the site
- Rent: $416,664 per annum* + GST
- 10 + 5 year lease (December 2011 lease commencement)
- Total strata area: 1,218sqm*
- 10 undercroft car spaces & a single lock up garage
- Strong Chinese demographic ideal for restaurant tenants
- Can be sold as leased or with vacant possession for owner occupiers

The property will be offered for sale by way of Expressions of Interest closing on Wednesday 8 November 2017 at 6:00PM AEST 

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the client. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence

For further details, please contact the exclusive CBRE selling agents.

*Approximate

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: EXCEPTIONALLY WELL-LOCATED RESTAURANT WITH OUTDOOR DINING

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Next to Concert Hall, Library & Theatre

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Chatswood Concourse, located at the centre of Victoria Avenue, is home to a thriving retail precinct with a focus on food & beverage, 1,000 seat concert hall, 500 seat theatre, 5,000sqm library, numerous function spaces and a 400 capacity car park. 
 
Opened in 2011, the Council owned development services the local community of over 356,000 people* as well as the commercial office market and broader North Shore catchment. 
 
CBRE is proud to take to market two flagship food & beverage opportunities in this tightly held precinct. 
 
Shop 1
 
- 151sqm* internally
- 91.4sqm* covered external seating area facing the concert hall entry + additional 22sqm* external seating area on Victoria Avenue
- 30sqm* basement storage 
- Located at the pedestrian traffic lights, the premises has huge exposure to both Victoria Avenue and the entrance to the concert hall and library
- Connected to grease, exhaust, gas and air conditioning 
- Partial fit out in place (if required) or can be brought back to a cold shell
- Parking available (if required)
- Liquor licence in place
 
Shop 4 & 6
                
- 474sqm* internally spread over two levels. Opportunity to be split if required (ground floor  124sqm*, level 1  350sqm*)
- 61.3sqm* covered external seating area facing concert hall entry
- 25sqm* basement storage 
- Exclusive use internal lift & stairwell
- Huge double storey glass shopfront overlooking The Concourse and Victoria Avenue
- Connected to grease, exhaust, gas and air conditioning 
- Cold shell ready for a tenants fit out
- Parking available (if required)
- Liquor licence in place
 
The Concourse is centred in between Chatswood Interchange (bus and rail), Chatswood Chase and Westfield Shopping Centre. Chatswood CBD is a dominant retail destination supported by extensive residential and commercial buildings with a trade area retail spend currently valued at $6.5billion* per annum.

For further details or to arrange an inspection, please call James Beerworth 0499 038 215 or Amy Pfeiffer 0401 198 401. 

*Approx.
